1. Setup automount:

    To setup automount, edit file /etc/fstab with sudo
    Then add following command
    NTFS:
    > UUID=71E9955B634E6774 /media/ocr5/backup ntfs uid=1000,gid=1000,umask=0022,sync,auto,rw 0 0

    Use id -u <username> to get the userid and id -g <username> to get the groupid.

    EXT4:
    > UUID=84d5111b-ae28-4fea-9f61-f182033621d5 /media/huanlv/data ext4 defaults 0 0

    To check UUID of disk use:
    > sudo blkid

2. Setup crontab on machine
    Before set crontab on machine, copy backup script to test machine.
    Prepare shell script files execute the work, then configure crontab by command:

    crontab -e

    Then you will add the command with following syntax:

    Syntax of crontab (field description)

    1 2 3 4 5 /path_to_script.sh

    Where,

    1: Minute (0-59)
    2: Hours (0-23)
    3: Day (0-31)
    4: Month (0-12 [12 == December])
    5: Day of the week(0-7 [7 or 0 == sunday])
    /path_to_script.sh â€“ Script or command name to schedule